        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Symptom: When an exception occurs during development, we see the exception class and message being rethrown from dispatch(); however, the stack trace, which can prove very useful is lost. \n\nBecause php does not have a \"rethrow\" feature that preserves the exception, we should either refractor to not catch exceptions while throwExceptions() is enabled or wrap the original exception to preserve the stack trace.\n"
        },
